radiographic_examinations.findings: The tip of the right PICC projects over the distal SVC. An enteric tube extends below the level of the diaphragm but beyond the field of view of this radiograph. The lung volumes are low. Linear atelectasis is re-visualized in the right midlung. There is no new consolidation, pneumothorax or large pleural effusion. The size of the cardiac silhouette is unchanged. Surgical clips project over the low neck at midline.
